    <h1 class="text-center mb-4">Top 20 Must-Visit Places in Gambia with Mr. Gibs</h1>
    <div class="row g-4">
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h2>Kachikally Crocodile Pool</h2>
            <p>Experience the thrill of close encounters with crocodiles in their natural habitat at this sacred pool in
                Bakau.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h2>Abuko Nature Reserve</h2>
            <p>Gambia's oldest wildlife reserve, home to a rich diversity of birds and animals, nestled within lush
                forests.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h2>Bijilo Forest Park</h2>
            <p>A serene coastal park offering shaded trails, a variety of wildlife, and peaceful spots to enjoy
                nature.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h2>Albert Market</h2>
            <p>Located in Banjul, this bustling market is the perfect place to shop for fabrics, crafts, and fresh
                produce.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h2>Tanji Village Museum</h2>
            <p>Explore Gambian culture through exhibits on traditional dwellings, crafts, and ways of life at this
                open-air museum.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h2>Sanyang Beach</h2>
            <p>One of the most beautiful beaches in Gambia, offering pristine sands, clear waters, and a relaxing
                ambiance.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h2>Makasutu Culture Forest</h2>
            <p>A mystical forest rich in biodiversity and culture, offering guided tours, canoe trips, and cultural
                performances.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h2>National Museum of Gambia</h2>
            <p>Delve into the history, culture, and heritage of Gambia with a visit to this informative museum in
                Banjul.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h2>Kunta Kinteh Island</h2>
            <p>Formerly James Island, this UNESCO World Heritage site offers a poignant look into the history of the
                transatlantic slave trade.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h2>Fort Bullen</h2>
            <p>This historic fort offers stunning views and a unique insight into Gambia's colonial history.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h2>Stone Circles of Senegambia</h2>
            <p>Discover the mysterious ancient stone circles spread across Gambia and Senegal, believed to be burial
                sites.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h2>Gambia River National Park</h2>
            <p>Experience the beauty and diversity of the Gambia River with a boat tour, spotting wildlife and scenic
                landscapes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h2>Pipeline Mosque</h2>
            <p>A significant religious site in The Gambia, known for its beautiful architecture and spiritual
                atmosphere.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h2>Wassu Stone Circles</h2>
            <p>Visit the Wassu Stone Circles, a UNESCO World Heritage site, known for its archaeological
                significance.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h2>Banjul State House</h2>
            <p>The official residence of the President of Gambia, notable for its architectural beauty and historical
                importance.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h2>Arch 22</h2>
            <p>A striking monument and museum offering panoramic views of Banjul from its top, commemorating a military
                coup.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h2>Juffureh Village</h2>
            <p>Known for its connection to Alex Haley's "Roots", this village offers a deep dive into Gambian history
                and culture.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h2>Kotu Beach</h2>
            <p>A popular spot for tourists, known for its sandy beaches, local markets, and vibrant nightlife.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h2>Gunjur Village</h2>
            <p>Experience the authentic Gambian village life and explore the local culture, traditions, and beautiful
                beaches.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <h2>Serekunda Market</h2>
            <p>The largest market in Gambia, offering everything from textiles to electronics, and a true taste of local
                life.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
